description:
Even here in the Philippines, you can find vegan stuff from other cuisines, like at this Indian grocery store called Assad Mini Mart and Cafe in Manila. 

It was fun to see the traditional vegan stuff like spices, beans, nuts, flour, and fruits, as well as the new ones like vegan mayonnaise and mock meats. And their samosas are vegan, so I got them and ate them at their cafe next door.

This one was at their main headquarters in Manila, but they also have other smaller stores throughout Metro Manila. 

As a vegan for over 15 years, the fun part about this journey is that I never get to stop learning and discovering new vegan finds. I invite you also to discover the joys of exploring vegan food and way of living. It can be quite an adventure!

Exact location:
Midtown Executive Homes
1268 United Nations Avenue, Manila
